    <div class="faq-a" id="is-seo-being-phased-out"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>No. Every major shift in search has been framed as the end of SEO. Mobile, voice, zero-click results, and now AI Overviews have all been called the end of SEO. None of them eliminated the underlying work. They reshaped which signals matter. The constant is that pages have to be discoverable, indexable, and trustworthy. The mechanics live in your code.</p></div></div>
